<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Male</emphasis>
: macropterous, with antennomere 9 about six times as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Hybristodryinus castaneus sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C head and mesosoma, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, ventral view E antenna F fore wing." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.57792.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512986" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">1E</figureCitation>
); face without long deep longitudinal furrow (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Hybristodryinus castaneus sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C head and mesosoma, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, ventral view E antenna F fore wing." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.57792.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512986" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">1D</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of vertex not deeply excavated medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Hybristodryinus castaneus sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C head and mesosoma, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, ventral view E antenna F fore wing." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.57792.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512986" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">1C</figureCitation>
); lateral ocelli not touching occipital carina; notauli complete, posteriorly separated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Hybristodryinus castaneus sp. nov., male, holotype A habitus, dorsal view B habitus, ventral view C head and mesosoma, dorsal view D head and mesosoma, ventral view E antenna F fore wing." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.81.57792.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/512986" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
